title: Wisconsin Firm Recalls Beef Stick Products That May Contain Foreign Materials
summary: WASHINGTON, October 22, 2010 - Klement Sausage Company, Inc., a Milwaukee, Wisc., establishment, is recalling approximately 2,740 pounds of beef stick products that may contain foreign materials, the U.S. Department of Agriculture's Food Safety and Inspection Service (FSIS) announced today. The products subject to recall...
impacted_products: 8-ounce packages of "MARKET PANTRY BEEF STICKS, ORIGINAL."
